gomodel:SYNGO_2958  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: [Fig.4: \"Presynaptic β-Catenin Is Sufficient to Promote Excitatory Synaptic Transmission and Spinogenesis\"\nFig.6: \"Enhanced β-Catenin Expression Induces Enlargement of Synaptophysin Puncta In Vivo\"\nFig.7: \"The Cadherin/Catenin Complex Regulates Release Probability\"]\n\nFig.8: \"The Cadherin/Catenin Complex Functions through p140Cap\"\n\nNote:\n- Fig.5 \"The Effect of β-Catenin Depends on Its Cell Adhesion, but Not Its Transcriptional Function\"\n- Conclusion: beta-catenin regulates organization of the presynapse via p140Cap.. Experimental description: - \"The full-length p140Cap (gene name: SRCIN1) was obtained from P14 mouse cortical cDNA ...\"\n- \"Acute slices were prepared in a sucrose-based cutting solution. Briefly, mice were deeply ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
